The paper discusses the challenge of detecting anomalous behavior in network traffic, which falls under the category of network security and intrusion detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of sparse linear algebra, associative arrays, and distributed databases, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the benchmarking of the analytics pipeline, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
